Samsung Health Integration requires a native Android application:

1. Register your app in Samsung Health Developer Portal
2. Add Samsung Health SDK to your Android project
3. Request permissions: com.samsung.android.providers.health.permission.READ
4. Use HealthDataResolver to query step count data
5. Implement a bridge to send data to your web app via WebView or API

Example Android code:
\`\`\`java
HealthDataResolver resolver = new HealthDataResolver(store, null);
HealthDataResolver.ReadRequest request = new ReadRequest.Builder()
    .setDataType(HealthConstants.StepCount.HEALTH_DATA_TYPE)
    .setLocalTimeRange(startTime, endTime)
    .build();
resolver.read(request).setResultListener(result -> {
    // Process step count data
    int totalSteps = 0;
    for (HealthData data : result) {
        totalSteps += data.getInt(HealthConstants.StepCount.COUNT);
    }
    // Send to web app
});
\`\`\`

For web integration, you'll need to:
- Build a companion Android app
- Implement a backend API to receive step data
